<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The decision on the placement or provision of care may be made in the requesting State only if the Central Authority or other competent authority of the requested State has consented to the placement or provision of care, taking into account the child's best interests. </inglise>
<eesti> Paigutamise v&otilde;i hooldamise otsuse v&otilde;ib teha taotluse esitanud riigis &uuml;ksnes siis, kui keskasutus v&otilde;i muu taotletava riigi p&auml;dev asutus on paigutamise v&otilde;i hooldamisega n&otilde;us, v&otilde;ttes arvesse lapse parimad huvid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 34 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 34 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a measure of protection is contemplated, the competent authorities under the Convention, if the situation of the child so requires, may request any authority of another Contracting State which has information relevant to the protection of the child to communicate such information. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kavandatakse kaitsemeedet, v&otilde;ib p&auml;dev asutus k&auml;esoleva konventsiooni alusel, kui lapse olukord seda n&otilde;uab, taotleda teise osalisriigi asutuselt, kellel on lapse kaitse seisukohalt olulist teavet, sellise teabe edastamist. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> A Contracting State may declare that requests under paragraph 1 shall be communicated to its authorities only through its Central Authority. </inglise>
<eesti> Osalisriik v&otilde;ib teatada, et l&otilde;ike 1 alusel tehtavad taotlused tuleb edastada tema asutustele &uuml;ksnes keskasutuse kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 35 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 35 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities of a Contracting State may request the authorities of another Contracting State to assist in the implementation of measures of protection taken under this Convention, especially in securing the effective exercise of rights of access as well as of the right to maintain direct contacts on a regular basis. </inglise>
<eesti> Osalisriigi p&auml;devad asutused v&otilde;ivad paluda teise osalisriigi asutustel abistada k&auml;esoleva konventsiooni alusel v&otilde;etud kaitsemeetmete rakendamisel, eelk&otilde;ige tagades lapsega suhtlemise &otilde;iguse ja regulaarsete otsekontaktide &otilde;iguse t&otilde;husa teostamise. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The authorities of a Contracting State in which the child does not habitually reside may, on the request of a parent residing in that State who is seeking to obtain or to maintain access to the child, gather information or evidence and may make a finding on the suitability of that parent to exercise access and on the conditions under which access is to be exercised. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle osalisriigi asutused, kus laps alaliselt ei ela, koguvad selles riigis elava vanema taotlusel, kes p&uuml;&uuml;ab saada v&otilde;i s&auml;ilitada lapsega suhtlemise &otilde;igust, teavet v&otilde;i t&otilde;endeid ning teevad otsuse selle kohta, kas vanem on sobiv kasutama lapsega suhtlemise &otilde;igust, ja lapsega suhtlemise tingimuste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> An authority exercising jurisdiction under Articles 5 to 10 to determine an application concerning access to the child, shall admit and consider such information, evidence and finding before reaching its decision. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutus, kellel on artiklite 5-10 alusel p&auml;devus lahendada lapsega suhtlemise &otilde;igusega seotud avaldus, v&otilde;tab enne otsuse tegemist sellise teabe, t&otilde;endid ja j&auml;relduse vastu ning arvestab seda. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> An authority having jurisdiction under Articles 5 to 10 to decide on access may adjourn a proceeding pending the outcome of a request made under paragraph 2, in particular, when it is considering an application to restrict or terminate access rights granted in the State of the child's former habitual residence. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutus, kellel on artiklite 5-10 alusel p&auml;devus otsustada lapsega suhtlemise &otilde;iguse &uuml;le, v&otilde;ib peatada menetluse l&otilde;ike 2 alusel esitatud taotluse tulemuste selgumiseni, eelk&otilde;ige juhul, kui ta kaalub avaldust piirata v&otilde;i v&otilde;tta &auml;ra lapsega suhtlemise &otilde;igused, mis anti lapse endises alalises elukohariigis. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Nothing in this Article shall prevent an authority having jurisdiction under Articles 5 to 10 from taking provisional measures pending the outcome of the request made under paragraph 2. </inglise>
<eesti> Mitte miski k&auml;esolevas artiklis ei takista artiklite 5-10 alusel p&auml;deval asutusel v&otilde;tta ajutisi meetmeid kuni l&otilde;ike 2 alusel esitatud taotluse tulemuste selgumiseni. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 36 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 36 </eesti>
<inglise> In any case where the child is exposed to a serious danger, the competent authorities of the Contracting State where measures for the protection of the child have been taken or are under consideration, if they are informed that the child's residence has changed to, or that the child is present in another State, shall inform the authorities of that other State about the danger involved and the measures taken or under consideration. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui last &auml;hvardab t&otilde;sine oht ja kui selle osalisriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele, kus on v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i kaalumisel meetmed lapse kaitseks, on teatatud, et lapse elukoht on muutunud v&otilde;i et laps asub teises riigis, teavitavad nimetatud asutused selle teise riigi asutusi seonduvast ohust ning v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i kaalumisel olevatest meetmetest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 37 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 37 </eesti>
<inglise> An authority shall not request or transmit any information under this Chapter if to do so would, in its opinion, be likely to place the child's person or property in danger, or constitute a serious threat to the liberty or life of a member of the child's family. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutus ei taotle ega edasta teavet k&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki alusel, kui see v&otilde;ib tema arvates seada ohtu lapse v&otilde;i tema vara v&otilde;i kujutada t&otilde;sist ohtu lapse perekonnaliikme vabadusele v&otilde;i elule. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 38 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 38 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to the possibility of imposing reasonable charges for the provision of services, Central Authorities and other public authorities of Contracting States shall bear their own costs in applying the provisions of this Chapter. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks v&otilde;imalust kehtestada m&otilde;istlikud tasud teenuste osutamise eest, kannavad osalisriikide keskasutused ja teised riigiasutused k&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki s&auml;tteid kohaldades oma kulud ise. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Any Contracting State may enter into agreements with one or more other Contracting States concerning the allocation of charges. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga osalisriik v&otilde;ib tasude jaotamise suhtes s&otilde;lmida kokkuleppe &uuml;he v&otilde;i enama osalisriigiga. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 39 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 39 </eesti>
<inglise> Any Contracting State may enter into agreements with one or more other Contracting States with a view to improving the application of this Chapter in their mutual relations. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga osalisriik v&otilde;ib s&otilde;lmida kokkuleppe &uuml;he v&otilde;i enama osalisriigiga, et parandada k&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki kohaldamist nende omavahelistes suhetes. </eesti>
<inglise> The States which have concluded such an agreement shall transmit a copy to the depositary of the Convention. </inglise>
