<inglise> Article 46 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 46 </eesti>
<inglise> A Contracting State in which different systems of law or sets of rules of law apply to the protection of the child and his or her property shall not be bound to apply the rules of the Convention to conflicts solely between such different systems or sets of rules of law. </inglise>
<eesti> Osalisriik, kus lapse isiku v&otilde;i vara kaitse suhtes kohaldatakse eri &otilde;iguss&uuml;steeme v&otilde;i -normistikke, ei ole kohustatud kohaldama konventsiooni eeskirju &uuml;ksnes selliste eri s&uuml;steemide v&otilde;i &otilde;igusnormistike konfliktide suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 47 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 47 </eesti>
<inglise> In relation to a State in which two or more systems of law or sets of rules of law with regard to any matter dealt with in this Convention apply in different territorial units: 1. any reference to habitual residence in that State shall be construed as referring to habitual residence in a territorial unit; </inglise>
<eesti> Sellises riigis, kus k&auml;esoleva konventsiooniga reguleeritud k&uuml;simuste suhtes kohaldatakse erinevates territoriaal&uuml;ksustes kahte v&otilde;i enamat &otilde;iguss&uuml;steemi v&otilde;i -normistikku, t&auml;hendab viide: </eesti>
<inglise> 2. any reference to the presence of the child in that State shall be construed as referring to presence in a territorial unit; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) alalisele elukohale selles riigis viidet alalisele elukohale territoriaal&uuml;ksuses; </eesti>
<inglise> 3. any reference to the location of property of the child in that State shall be construed as referring to location of property of the child in a territorial unit; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) lapse asumisele selles riigis viidet lapse asumisele territoriaal&uuml;ksuses; 3) lapse vara asukohale selles riigis viidet lapse vara asukohale territoriaal&uuml;ksuses; </eesti>
<inglise> 4. any reference to the State of which the child is a national shall be construed as referring to the territorial unit designated by the law of that State or, in the absence of relevant rules, to the territorial unit with which the child has the closest connection; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) riigile, mille kodanikuks laps on, viidet selle riigi &otilde;iguses m&auml;&auml;ratud territoriaal&uuml;ksusele v&otilde;i asjakohaste eeskirjade puudumisel viidet territoriaal&uuml;ksusele, millega lapsel on k&otilde;ige tihedam seos; </eesti>
<inglise> 5. any reference to the State whose authorities are seised of an application for divorce or legal separation of the child's parents, or for annulment of their marriage, shall be construed as referring to the territorial unit whose authorities are seised of such application; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) riigile, mille asutustele on esitatud abielulahutuse, lapse vanemate lahuselu v&otilde;i abielu kehtetuks tunnistamise taotlus, viidet territoriaal&uuml;ksusele, mille asutustele on esitatud selline taotlus; </eesti>
<inglise> 6. any reference to the State with which the child has a substantial connection shall be construed as referring to the territorial unit with which the child has such connection; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) riigile, millega lapsel on m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rne seos, viidet territoriaal&uuml;ksusele, millega lapsel on nimetatud seos; </eesti>
<inglise> 7. any reference to the State to which the child has been removed or in which he or she has been retained shall be construed as referring to the relevant territorial unit to which the child has been removed or in which he or she has been retained; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) riigile, kuhu laps on viidud v&otilde;i kus teda on hoitud, viidet asjakohasele territoriaal&uuml;ksusele, kuhu laps on viidud v&otilde;i kus teda on hoitud; </eesti>
<inglise> 8. any reference to bodies or authorities of that State, other than Central Authorities, shall be construed as referring to those authorised to act in the relevant territorial unit; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) selle riigi organitele v&otilde;i asutustele, v&auml;lja arvatud keskasutused, viidet nendele organitele v&otilde;i asutustele, kellel on lubatud tegutseda territoriaal&uuml;ksuses; </eesti>
<inglise> 9. any reference to the law or procedure or authority of the State in which a measure has been taken shall be construed as referring to the law or procedure or authority of the territorial unit in which such measure was taken; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) selle riigi &otilde;igusele, menetlusele v&otilde;i asutusele, kus meede v&otilde;eti, viidet selle territoriaal&uuml;ksuse &otilde;igusele, menetlusele v&otilde;i asutusele, kus meede v&otilde;eti; </eesti>
<inglise> 10. any reference to the law or procedure or authority of the requested State shall be construed as referring to the law or procedure or authority of the territorial unit in which recognition or enforcement is sought. </inglise>
<eesti> 10) selle riigi &otilde;igusele, menetlusele v&otilde;i asutusele, kellele taotlus esitati, viidet selle territoriaal&uuml;ksuse &otilde;igusele, menetlusele v&otilde;i asutusele, kellelt taotletakse tunnustamist v&otilde;i t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 48 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 48 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of identifying the applicable law under Chapter III, in relation to a State which comprises two or more territorial units each of which has its own system of law or set of rules of law in respect of matters covered by this Convention, the following rules apply: </inglise>
<eesti> III peat&uuml;ki alusel kohaldatava &otilde;iguse kindlakstegemisel riigi suhtes, mis koosneb kahest v&otilde;i enamast territoriaal&uuml;ksusest, millest iga&uuml;hel on k&auml;esoleva konventsiooniga h&otilde;lmatud k&uuml;simuste suhtes oma &otilde;iguss&uuml;steem v&otilde;i -normistik, kohaldatakse j&auml;rgmisi eeskirju: </eesti>
<inglise> a) if there are rules in force in such a State identifying which territorial unit's law is applicable, the law of that unit applies; </inglise>
<eesti> a) kui sellises riigis on j&otilde;us eeskirjad, millega saab kindlaks teha, millise territoriaal&uuml;ksuse &otilde;igus on kohaldatav, siis kohaldatakse selle &uuml;ksuse &otilde;igust; </eesti>
<inglise> b) in the absence of such rules, the law of the relevant territorial unit as defined in Article 47 applies. </inglise>
<eesti> b) selliste eeskirjade puudumisel kohaldatakse asjakohase territoriaal&uuml;ksuse &otilde;igust, nagu on s&auml;testatud artiklis 47. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 49 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 49 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of identifying the applicable law under Chapter III, in relation to a State which has two or more systems of law or sets of rules of law applicable to different categories of persons in respect of matters covered by this Convention, the following rules apply: </inglise>
<eesti> III peat&uuml;ki alusel kohaldatava &otilde;iguse kindlakstegemisel riigi suhtes, kus on kaks v&otilde;i enam &otilde;iguss&uuml;steemi v&otilde;i -normistikku, mis kehtivad isikute eri kategooriate suhtes k&auml;esoleva konventsiooniga h&otilde;lmatud k&uuml;simustes, kohaldatakse j&auml;rgmisi eeskirju: </eesti>
